modules.description: Encodes and decodes data using common formats like JSON and URL-encoded strings, and handles compression based on HTTP headers. It processes request bodies and response bodies, supporting types such as strings, maps, and lists. It is used to automatically compress HTTP responses when clients support it, improving network efficiency.

Provides middleware to compress HTTP responses based on the client's preferred encoding and decompress incoming request bodies when supported. Works with HTTP messages, response bodies, and encoding headers like Accept-Encoding and Content-Encoding. Used to automatically compress HTML, JSON, or other text-based responses, and to handle decompression of incoming data when required.
